     <div type="to_the_reader">
   <pb facs="4"/>
   <head>To the iudicious Reader.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>THou seest this great <hi>VVorld</hi> (<hi>Reader</hi>) &amp; perchāce</l>
      <l>Thine Eie is cloid with often seeing it;</l>
      <l>Then see the <hi>Lesse</hi> with noe lesse circumstance,</l>
      <l>Aud with <hi>VVittes</hi> Eie, that <hi>Monarchy</hi> of <hi>VVitte.</hi>
         <note place="margin">Microcosmos.</note>
      </l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>The <hi>Heav'ns</hi> and <hi>Earth,</hi> do make the greater <hi>VVorld</hi>;</l>
      <l>And <hi>Soule</hi> and <hi>Bodie,</hi> make the <hi>Lesse</hi> (we prove:)</l>
      <l>The <hi>Heav'ns</hi> doe moue the <hi>Earth,</hi> &amp; they are whirld</l>
      <l>By <hi>Him,</hi> that makes the <hi>Soule,</hi> the <hi>Body</hi> moue.<note place="margin">Primus Moto.</note>
      </l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Who conquers <hi>it</hi> (at least) are <hi>Monarchs</hi> great,</l>
      <l>Greater then those that conquered the <hi>greater</hi>;</l>
      <l>For, from their <hi>goodnesse Men</hi> their <hi>greatnes</hi> gette,</l>
      <l>And they are <hi>best,</hi> that doe subdue the <hi>better</hi>:<note place="margin">Prover. 16 32.</note>
      </l>
      <l>The great <hi>VVorld's good,</hi> but <hi>better</hi> is the <hi>least</hi>:<note place="margin">Things living though never so small, are better then liveles things, though never so great.</note>
      </l>
      <l>Then <hi>view</hi> it, to <hi>subdue</hi> it, thou wert best.</l>
      <signed>IOHN DAVIS.</signed>
   </lg>
</div>
